&lt;h1&gt;🐾 Certified Veterinary Technician (CVT/RVT/LVT) Wanted!&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;isSelectedEnd&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Love animals? Obsessed with great medicine? Want to work somewhere that actually appreciates your skills?&lt;/strong&gt; We&#39;ve got a spot for you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;isSelectedEnd&quot;&gt;We&#39;re looking for a &lt;strong&gt;Certified Veterinary Technician&lt;/strong&gt; who&#39;s compassionate, confident, and ready to make a real difference every single day. If you&#39;re the type of person who loves patient care, enjoys educating pet parents, and thrives on teamwork, we&#39;d love to meet you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;isSelectedEnd&quot;&gt;Whether you&#39;re monitoring anesthesia, helping a nervous puppy feel safe, or celebrating a patient&#39;s recovery with their family, you&#39;ll be an essential part of what makes our hospital amazing.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;✨ What You&#39;ll Be Doing&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;isSelectedEnd&quot;&gt;No two days are exactly the same, and that&#39;s what makes this job fun! You&#39;ll:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul data-spread=&quot;false&quot;&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide exceptional nursing care for our patients from check-in to discharge.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor anesthesia and assist during surgical and dental procedures.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collect lab samples, run diagnostics, and perform treatments with confidence.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Administer medications, vaccines, and fluid therapy as directed by our veterinarians.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Educate pet parents about medications, preventive care, nutrition, recovery plans, and everything in between.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build lasting relationships with clients by making them feel heard, informed, and supported.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work alongside our veterinarians and support staff to deliver top-tier medical care.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Keep accurate medical records and maintain a smooth workflow throughout the day.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help keep our hospital clean, organized, and running efficiently.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Jump in wherever needed—because teamwork really is our superpower.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;🩺 What We&#39;re Looking For&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;isSelectedEnd&quot;&gt;We&#39;re searching for someone who&#39;s more than just qualified—we want someone who genuinely loves what they do.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;isSelectedEnd&quot;&gt;You should have:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul data-spread=&quot;false&quot;&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Graduation from an accredited Veterinary Technician program (Associate Degree).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Current CVT, RVT, or LVT credentials (or be eligible for licensing).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Successful completion of the Veterinary Technician National Examination (VTNE).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in a veterinary hospital (general practice, ER, or specialty experience is a plus!).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong technical skills and confidence handling patients of all sizes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication skills with both clients and teammates.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A positive attitude and the ability to stay calm during busy days.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Great time management and organizational skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A passion for learning and continuing to grow your skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A team-first mindset—you celebrate wins together and jump in to help without being asked.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A love for pets (obviously ❤️).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;💚 Why You&#39;ll Love Working Here&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;isSelectedEnd&quot;&gt;We&#39;re serious about great medicine—but we also believe work should be enjoyable.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;isSelectedEnd&quot;&gt;Here&#39;s what you can expect:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul data-spread=&quot;false&quot;&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Competitive pay based on experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comprehensive benefits package starting DAY ONE.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;CE allowance and license

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Associate Veterinarian&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Chessie Lane Animal Hospital&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location:&lt;/strong&gt; Ottawa, Illinois&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Opportunity&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;Looking for a veterinary role that comes with a genuinely great lifestyle? Chessie Lane Animal Hospital in Ottawa, IL is looking for a full-time Associate Veterinarian to join our friendly, long‑standing team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We&#39;ve proudly served the Ottawa community for nearly 30 years, and our commitment to compassionate, high‑quality care earned us the 2023 Times Readers’ Choice Award for Favorite Veterinary Clinic. If you’re hoping to join a clinic where teamwork, positivity, and excellent patient care all matter equally, this may be your perfect fit.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why You’ll Love Ottawa, IL&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;Ottawa is one of Illinois’ best-kept secrets—a historic, scenic town located at the confluence of the Illinois and Fox Rivers. Living and working here means enjoying:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Beautiful outdoor spaces including Starved Rock, Matthiessen, and Buffalo Rock State Parks&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A welcoming, community‑oriented atmosphere&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A charming downtown full of local restaurants, coffee shops, and boutiques&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Affordable living with an easygoing Midwest vibe&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Endless opportunities for hiking, kayaking, biking, and weekend adventures&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you want small‑town warmth with big natural beauty, Ottawa delivers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Our Team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;Chessie Lane is a supportive, low‑drama workplace where collaboration is valued and kindness is the norm. We work hard, we communicate openly, and we genuinely enjoy each other’s company. Our clinic is fully equipped with:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Digital radiography&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;In-house Idexx lab&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ultrasound&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Dentistry capabilities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Soft tissue surgery&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Full GP services&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We believe in giving our doctors the support, tools, and autonomy they need to do their best work while still maintaining work‑life balance.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform small animal wellness exams, sick visits, and diagnostic workups&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide soft tissue surgery and dentistry services&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Utilize digital imaging and in-house diagnostics&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain accurate patient records&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with and mentor support staff&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build strong client relationships through clear communication and compassionate care&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What We’re Looking For&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A DVM/VMD graduate from an AVMA-accredited program&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Illinois veterinary license (or ability to obtain prior to start)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong clinical and surgical skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A collaborative, communicative team player&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Commitment to continued learning and professional growth&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A compassionate approach to both pets and people&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Compensation &amp;amp; Benefits&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Compensation: $135,000–$165,000 base salary&amp;nbsp;
